explanation: The solution utilizes a list to store locations as tuples of (name, score). It sorts the list in descending order based on score and ascending order based on name when a new location is added. This ensures efficient retrieval of the best location in O(1) time. The sorting operation takes O(N log N) time, making the overall time complexity O(N log N) for adding locations. Space complexity is O(N) due to storing all locations. Energy implications are low as the operations are primarily memory-based.

